OL,3,GWest Midlands
OL,4,
OL,5,CThis Evening and Tonight:FMostly dry
OL,6,Fand rather humid this evening with the
OL,7,Fodd drizzly outbreak possible, but
OL,8,Fthis tending to become mostly confined
OL,9,Fto the hills overnight. Remaining dry
OL,10,Fand very mild for most and staying a
OL,11,Flittle breezy, especially over the
OL,12,Fhills.
OL,13,
OL,14,CFriday:FCloudy for many first thing
OL,15,Fwith showery rain over the Peak
OL,16,FDistrict. Generally dry by the
OL,17,Fafternoon with sunny spells
OL,18,Fdeveloping. Feeling warmer than on
OL,19,FThursday but remaining breezy.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
